content:
When quoting and endorsing Auto products, our pricing services use the product model data, product rating procedure, and pricing formulas to price coverages, vehicles, and total premiums.

The service:

* Pulls data from the Commercial Auto product model to form the rating input data.
* Calls the rating procedure and rating input data to calculate coverage prices.
* Rolls up coverage prices to vehicles using the vehicle pricing formula.
* Rolls up vehicle prices to the total (quoted) premium price.

We use the CommercialAutoRating Integration Procedure, which calculates coverage prices for the Commercial Auto product. The quote business process calls this rating procedure to calculate prices for quotes.

To understand how the rating procedure works, see Rating Procedures and try simulating the rating procedure on the Commercial Auto product model. Then, view the quote flows to see how the Auto Application rates products for quotes.

We use lookup tables with the autoRateCommercialVehicles expression set to identify ratings for auto insurance products. You can modify these tables to reflect your ratings.

After the rating procedure returns coverage prices, Vlocity uses product model pricing formulas to roll up prices and calculate premiums per vehicle and total policy premium.
title: Commercial Auto Insurance Rating Procedure
